12-13 August - Chocolate Italian Cookies (Almond)

- 2   eggs
- 1/2 cup oil
- 4   cups flour
- 2   cups sugar
- 2   teaspoon baking powder
- 1   tablespoon cinnamon
- 1   teaspoon cloves
- 1/2 teaspoon ginger
- 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
- 3/4 cup chocolate chips 
- 1   teaspoon lemon rind
- 1/2 cup chopped almonds
-     water as needed

Sift dry ingredients and set aside. Ina large bowl beat eggs, add oil and blend well. Add to dry ingredients. Add nuts and chocolate chips. If dough is too stiff add water as needed. Bake in a preheated 375F oven and in greased baking sheet for 10-15 minutes. Make rolls and cut on a slant (slices) while warm. 